Mix all the ingredients together in a #small mixing bowl. Store in an airtight container until you are ready to use:
@dried onion flakes{1/4%cup}
@onion powder{1/4%tsp}
@parsley{1/4%tsp}
@beef bouillon granules{2%Tbsp}
@celery seed{1/8%tsp}
@paprika{1/8%tsp}
@pepper{1/8%tsp}

Whisk all seasonings together in a #bowl until combined. Use immediately or store in a sealed container. *Feel free to adjust the ratio to make whatever size of batch you would like

@dried oregano{1.5%tsp}
@dried marjoram{1%tsp}
@dried thyme{1%tsp}
@dried basil{0.5%tsp}
@dried rosemary{0.5%tsp}
@dried sage{0.5%tsp}

Combine all the ingredients in a #blender and process until smooth. For best results, chill for at least ~{1%hour} before using.

@firm silken tofu{1-12.3%oz pkg}
@apple cider vinegar{1%Tbsp}
@Dijon mustard{2%tsp}
@garlic powder{0.75%tsp}
@onion powder{0.75%tsp}
@salt{0.75%tsp}
@coconut or date sugar{0.5%tsp}

Combine all ingredients in a #small saucepan, bring to a simmer over medium heat and cook for ~{5%minutes}:
- @ketchup{2/3%cup}
- @cider vinegar{1/2%cup}
- @brown sugar{1/4%cup}
- @pimentón (smoked Spanish paprika){2%tsp}
- @cumin{1%tsp}
- @salt{1%tsp}
- @pepper{1%tsp}

cooklang:
Halve @leeks{2%bunch} lengthwise, remove root base, cut into coarse pieces and wash. Halve and peel the @onion{1%head}. Wash the @lemon{1} with hot water, finely rub off about 1 tsp of peel, cut it in half and squeeze out the juice. 

Add onion and leek to a #blender{}. Chop vegetables for ~{10%seconds}. Add @oil and @minced meat{500%g} to the #pan and fry for ~{5%minutes}. Add leeks, @cream{200%ml}, @processed cheese{200%g}, lemon peel and @vegetable broth{700%ml} and cook for ~{15%minutes} 

Season the soup with @salt{}, @pepper and lemon juice and serve on plates.

Make labneh with @yogurt{450%g}, @goat yogurt{450%g}, and @salt{0.5%tsp}
Spread labneh on plate with back of spoon
Add diced @black olives{20}, chopped @garlic clove{1}, zest from @lemon{1}, @parsely{1%tsp}, @oregano{1%tsp}, and @olive oil{100%ml}
Toast @pistachios{50%g} and roughly chop 
Spread olive mixture over labneh with nuts and a sprinkle of @paprika{pinch}

Dry toast @giant couscous{250%g} until some color ~{5%minutes}
Add @vegetable stock{500%ml}, @salt{1%tsp}, bring to boil, cover and simmer ~{10%minutes}
Remove from heat, let sit covered for ~{10%minutes}
Mix in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and let cool 
Soak @golden raisins{60%g} in boiling water for ~{10%minutes}
Toast and crush @cumin seed{1.5%tsp}
Toast @almond slivers{60%g}
Mix cumin, rasins, almond, chopped @dill{15%g}, and chopped @basil{15%g} into couscous 
Blend @parsely{15%g}, @olive oil{60%ml}, @garlic clove{1}, @salt, and @pepper until smooth 
Spoon oil on top before serving

